Show HN: Just Product Management Jobs – category specific job board
text:
Hey everyone,

Thanks for taking a look at a new project that we've been working on.

We feel like most job boards are missing the mark.

They are either large aggregators and have jobs across every job function imaginable.

Or, the niche job boards aren't very active...maybe because it is an add-on to the individual's blog or podcast.

We launched Just Product Management Jobs to combine laser focused job postings with high-value blog content that will be written by expert contributors covering topics around career advice and the latest trends + best practices in the Product Management industry.

We hope the mix of high quality jobs + high quality content = high value for Product Managers.

The design and user experience is also very simple and basic on purpose. A job board doesn't need to be complicated.

Thank you for taking a look. Let us know what you think - we appreciate your feedback!

Ask HN: Is Google seeking to strangle ChatGPT?
text:
It seems like Google search result quality is in rapid decline -- it's not respecting keyword operators, I'm getting more captchas, and I increasingly find myself resorting to use ChatGPT as a first-hop to get more granular when say, searching config docs for an open-source project, where the LLM may associate a keyword with a switch better than the docs Google will turn up...

Is this a tactic? Before ChatGPT is effectively monetized create excess traffic? Scrape ChatGPT logic with searchers doing the manual labor of porting those insights?

This looks like a miserable failure.
